Overview

Continued development of an enterprise-style PowerShell onboarding automation project that simulates how Identity & Access Management teams provision new employees into Active Directory.

Features Completed:
-Imported employee onboarding data from a CSV file.
-Validated the CSV file exists before processing.
-Verified employee records were successfully imported.
-Counted employee records.
-Displayed employee information for administrative verification.
-Built a PowerShell hashtable to map departments to Organizational Units.
-Dynamically determined the correct OU for each employee based on department.

Engineering Concepts Learned:
-PowerShell object manipulation
-CSV data processing
-Input validation
-Hashtable lookups
-Variable management
-Active Directory OU mapping
-Defensive programming principles

